'''斯瓦爾巴全球种子库'''（{{lang-no|Svalbard globale frøhvelv}}；{{lang-en|Svalbard Global Seed Vault}}）是[[挪威|挪威]]政府於[[北冰洋|北冰洋]][[斯瓦巴|斯瓦巴群岛]]上建造的[[非營利|非營利]]儲藏库，<ref name="Charles2006">{{cite journal |title=A 'Forever' Seed Bank Takes Root in the Arctic |journal=[[Science_(journal)|Science]] |last=Charles |first=Daniel |volume=312 |issue=5781 |pages=1730–1731 |date=2006-06-23 |doi=10.1126/science.312.5781.1730b |pmid=16794050}}</ref><ref name="bbc20060619">{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/sci/tech/5094450.stm |title=Work begins on Arctic seed vault |work=[[BBC_News|BBC News]] |date=2006-06-19 |accessdate=2011-07-03 |language=en-GB |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080213162937/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/sci/tech/5094450.stm |archive-date=2008-02-13 |dead-url=no }}</ref>用於保存全世界的[[农作物|农作物]][[种子|种子]]，為全球最大的種子庫。<ref name="李珮雲">{{Cite web|title=北極凍土下的這座倉庫 是末日後重建社會的唯一希望|url=https://www.chinatimes.com/hottopic/20170224001154-260809?chdtv|accessdate=2020-02-02|date=2017-02-24|author=李珮雲|work=中時電子報|language=zh-tw|archive-date=2020-10-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201013151343/https://www.chinatimes.com/hottopic/20170224001154-260809?chdtv|dead-url=no}}</ref>種子庫位於該群島首府[[隆雅市|隆雅市]]，由多個國際基因和生物組織合作{{NoteTag|時任{{le|全球作物多樣性信託基金|Crop Trust}}負責人暨[[美國|美國]][[農業|農業學]]者{{le|凱利‧福勒|Cary Fowler}}、{{le|國際農業研究磋商組織|CGIAR}}和{{le|國際生物多樣性|Bioversity International}}等組織，詳見[[斯瓦尔巴全球种子库#管理|管理]]及[[斯瓦尔巴全球种子库#历史|歷史]]二欄。}}、挪威政府出資興建，<ref name="natgeo201107">{{cite journal |url=http://ngm.nationalgeographic.com/2011/07/food-ark/siebert-text |title=Food Ark |journal=[[國家地理_(雜誌)|National Geographic]] |first=Charles |last=Siebert |volume=220 |issue=1 |pages=108–131 |date=2011-07 |oclc=741814684 |author= |access-date=2019-12-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180309140945/http://ngm.nationalgeographic.com/2011/07/food-ark/siebert-text |archive-date=2018-03-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Mellgren"/>是为了在大规模的区域性或[[全球災難危機|全球性危机]]出現期间防止某些种子基因的遺失，並進一步保存和備份種子的樣本，因此斯瓦爾巴全球種子庫亦被稱為'''末日種子庫'''<ref name="Alan Chiu">{{Cite web|title=冷岸群島全均氣溫升 3.5°C 致凍土融化 末日種子庫受威脅|url=https://www.thestandnews.com/nature/人類末日-冷岸群島全均氣溫升-3-5c-致凍土融化-末日種子庫受威脅/|date=2019-03-28|accessdate=2020-02-01|author=Alan Chiu|work=立場新聞 Stand News|language=zh-hk|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190814132125/https://thestandnews.com/nature/%E4%BA%BA%E9%A1%9E%E6%9C%AB%E6%97%A5-%E5%86%B7%E5%B2%B8%E7%BE%A4%E5%B3%B6%E5%85%A8%E5%9D%87%E6%B0%A3%E6%BA%AB%E5%8D%87-3-5c-%E8%87%B4%E5%87%8D%E5%9C%9F%E8%9E%8D%E5%8C%96-%E6%9C%AB%E6%97%A5%E7%A8%AE%E5%AD%90%E5%BA%AB%E5%8F%97%E5%A8%81%E8%84%85/|archive-date=2019-08-14|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="whatisnordgen">{{cite web |url=http://www.nordgen.org/index.php/en/content/view/full/467 |title=What is NordGen? |publisher=NordGen |accessdate=2012-04-15 |language=en |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100130234544/http://www.nordgen.org/index.php/en/content/view/full/467 |archivedate=2010-01-30 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=全球暖化導致北極升溫，將危及挪威全球種子庫的安全|url=https://tomorrowsci.com/environment/%e5%85%a8%e7%90%83%e6%9a%96%e5%8c%96-%e5%8c%97%e6%a5%b5%e5%8d%87%e6%ba%ab-%e6%8c%aa%e5%a8%81-%e5%85%a8%e7%90%83%e7%a8%ae%e5%ad%90%e5%ba%ab/|accessdate=2019-12-21|date=2019-02-23|last=EA|work=明日科學|language=zh-TW|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416200704/https://tomorrowsci.com/environment/%e5%85%a8%e7%90%83%e6%9a%96%e5%8c%96-%e5%8c%97%e6%a5%b5%e5%8d%87%e6%ba%ab-%e6%8c%aa%e5%a8%81-%e5%85%a8%e7%90%83%e7%a8%ae%e5%ad%90%e5%ba%ab/|archive-date=2019-04-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>或'''末日地窖'''<ref name="謝進盛"/>。

該計畫也獲得[[聯合國糧食及農業組織|聯合國糧食及農業組織]]的支持，被称为是全球[[农业|农业]]的“[[诺亚方舟|诺亚方舟]]”。<ref>{{Cite web|title=暖化影響永凍土 北極「末日種子庫」進水|url=https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/paper/1104068|accessdate=2019-12-21|date=2017-05-21|work=自由電子報|author=周虹汶|language=zh-tw|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191221144835/https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/paper/1104068|archive-date=2019-12-21|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theinitium.com/article/20170522-dailynews-seed-bank/|title=極北之地的五億顆種子：集世界之力打造農業版的「諾亞方舟」|author=蔣珮伊|date=2017-05-23|accessdate=2019-12-21|work=端傳媒|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191221144352/https://theinitium.com/article/20170522-dailynews-seed-bank/|archive-date=2019-12-21|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="FAO">{{Cite web|title=世界作物的一份保险单|url=http://www.fao.org/fao-stories/article/zh/c/1103282/|date=2018-02-21|accessdate=2019-12-21|author=Kent Nnadozie|work=聯合國糧食及農業組織|language=zh|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191221144357/http://www.fao.org/fao-stories/article/zh/c/1103282/|archive-date=2019-12-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>种子库依照[[挪威政治|挪威政府]]、{{le|全球作物多樣性信託基金|Crop Trust}}和{{le|北欧遗传资源中心|Nordic Genetic Resource Center}}（NordGen）達成的長期合作协议中之规定管理<ref name="whatisnordgen"/>。

斯瓦爾巴全球種子庫4,500萬[[挪威克朗|挪威克朗]]的建设费用由挪威政府全額資助<ref name="regjeringen-faq"/><ref name="Mellgren"/>，並和{{le|全球作物多樣性信託基金|Crop Trust}}共同負擔运营费用，該基金會的主要资金則来自[[比尔及梅琳达·盖茨基金会|比尔及梅琳达·盖茨基金会]]、各國政府及國際组织<ref name="trustdonors">{{cite web |url=http://www.croptrust.org/content/donors |title=Donors |work=Crop Trust |accessdate=2011-07-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150111000014/http://www.croptrust.org/content/donors |archive-date=2015-01-11 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="donate">{{Cite web|title=Our Donors|url=https://www.croptrust.org/about-us/donors/|accessdate=2019-12-21|work=Crop Trust|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726215214/https://www.croptrust.org/about-us/donors/|archive-date=2019-07-26|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 目的 ==
斯瓦爾巴全球种子库的建立是为保存全世界的[[農作物|農作物]]、植物種子，以防止在發生區域性或[[全球災難危機|全球性]]毀滅災害時，人類永久丧失某些[[粮食|粮食]]作物的基因，同時保護{{le|農業作物的多樣性|Crop diversity}}，挪威法律亦禁止在種子庫中存放[[基因改造作物|基因改造作物]]的種子。<ref>{{Cite web|title=世界還沒毀滅，替人類保存種子的「末日地窖」先受暖化之苦|url=https://www.thenewslens.com/article/68990|accessdate=2019-12-22|date=2017-05-23|last=Lo|work=The News Lens 關鍵評論網|language=zh-tw|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222053816/https://www.thenewslens.com/article/68990|archive-date=2019-12-22|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=FAQ about the Seed Vault|url=https://www.croptrust.org/our-work/svalbard-global-seed-vault/faq-about-the-vault/|accessdate=2019-12-22|work=Crop Trust|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203022237/https://www.croptrust.org/our-work/svalbard-global-seed-vault/faq-about-the-vault/|archive-date=2019-12-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>

根據《[[經濟學人|經濟學人]]》報導，斯瓦爾巴全球種子庫是全球第1,750個種子庫，也是維持農業作物的多樣性的備用地。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Banking against Doomsday, Banking against Doomsday|url=https://www.economist.com/international/2012/03/10/banking-against-doomsday|date=2012-03-10|accessdate=2019-12-22|journal=經濟學人|issn=0013-0613|author=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222053812/https://www.economist.com/international/2012/03/10/banking-against-doomsday|archive-date=2019-12-22|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 建造 ==
[[File:Cary_Fowler_2007.jpg|thumb]]
[[File:Entrance_tunnel_for_Svalbard_Global_Seed_Vault.jpg|thumb]]
斯瓦爾巴全球种子库由挪威[[建築師|建築師]]彼得·W·索德曼（Peter W. Søderman）設計，<ref name="Alyn">{{Cite web|title=Climate change forces emergency repairs to "failsafe" Arctic seed vault|url=https://www.dezeen.com/2017/06/14/climate-change-emergency-repairs-failsafe-arctic-svalbard-global-seed-vault/|author=Alyn Griffiths|accessdate=2020-02-03|date=2017-06-14|work=Dezeen|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514043147/https://www.dezeen.com/2017/06/14/climate-change-emergency-repairs-failsafe-arctic-svalbard-global-seed-vault/|archive-date=2019-05-14|dead-url=no}}</ref>建于[[斯瓦尔巴群岛|斯瓦尔巴群岛]][[永久凍土|永久冻土区]]一带的[[砂岩|砂岩]]山内部120米处，約[[海拔|海拔]]130米，由於該地發生[[地震|地震]]的機率低，<ref>{{Cite web|title=The “Doomsday Vault” in Norway in danger as world gets hotter|url=https://www.thevintagenews.com/2019/03/24/doomsday-vault/|accessdate=2020-01-01|date=2019-03-24|work=The Vintage News|author=Stefan Andrews|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200101160114/https://www.thevintagenews.com/2019/03/24/doomsday-vault/|archive-date=2020-01-01|dead-url=no}}</ref>且建築物的設計可承受[[芮氏規模|芮氏規模]]10.0的地震，<ref>{{Cite web|title=En moderne Noas ark|url=https://www.nrk.no/arkiv/artikkel/en-moderne-noas-ark-1.4926902|accessdate=2020-02-02|date=2008-02-25|last=Strømsnes|first=Roy|work=[[挪威廣播公司|NRK]]|language=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816140339/https://www.nrk.no/arkiv/artikkel/en-moderne-noas-ark-1.4926902|archive-date=2016-08-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>周圍也長年覆蓋[[永久凍土|永久凍土]]，即使島內的[[冰帽|冰帽]]融化，種子庫仍然能保持設備和建築物的干燥，<ref>{{Cite web|title=The vault holding humanity’s precious seeds is on thin ice|url=https://grist.org/article/the-vault-holding-humanitys-precious-seeds-is-on-thin-ice/|author=Zoya Teirstein|accessdate=2020-02-02|date=2019-03-27|work=Grist|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190530074617/https://grist.org/article/the-vault-holding-humanitys-precious-seeds-is-on-thin-ice/|archive-date=2019-05-30|dead-url=no}}</ref>建築物內的種子則被密封在三層鋁箔包裝中，並將其放入箱子內保存。<ref name="Woodward">{{Cite web|title=The world's 'doomsday seed vault' is built to store every crop on the planet, but the icy area that protects it is at risk|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/doomsday-seed-vault-in-danger-climate-change-2019-3|date=2019-03-31|accessdate=2019-12-22|last=Woodward|first=Aylin|work=Business Insider|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222063357/https://www.businessinsider.com/doomsday-seed-vault-in-danger-climate-change-2019-3|archive-date=2019-12-22|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Crop Trust3">{{Cite web|title=Svalbard Global Seed Vault|url=https://www.croptrust.org/our-work/svalbard-global-seed-vault/|accessdate=2019-12-22|work=Crop Trust|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190102082044/https://www.croptrust.org/our-work/svalbard-global-seed-vault/|archive-date=2019-01-02|dead-url=no}}</ref>為保護種子，人員須穿越400英尺長的隧道{{NoteTag|該隧道分別通往3個不同的種子儲存庫。<ref name="PMI">{{Cite web|title=Svalbard Global Seed Vault|url=https://mip.pmi.org/svalbard-global-seed-vault|accessdate=2020-02-02|work=PMI|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222151631/https://mip.pmi.org/svalbard-global-seed-vault|archive-date=2019-12-22|dead-url=no}}</ref>}}，並通過5道[[密碼鎖|密碼鎖]]門，才可進入地下的種子儲存庫。<ref name="Woodward"/>種子庫擁有3個種子儲存庫，每個儲存庫可儲藏150萬份種子，總共可儲存約450萬份。<ref>{{Cite web|title=More about the physical plant|url=https://www.regjeringen.no/en/topics/food-fisheries-and-agriculture/svalbard-global-seed-vault/mer-om-det-fysiske-anlegget/id2365142/|accessdate=2020-02-01|date=2015-02-23|work=農業和食品部|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203160018/https://www.regjeringen.no/en/topics/food-fisheries-and-agriculture/svalbard-global-seed-vault/mer-om-det-fysiske-anlegget/id2365142/|archive-date=2019-12-03|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Prisma Studio Tuomiopäivän holvissa|url=http://yle.fi/aihe/artikkeli/2012/03/19/prisma-studio-tuomiopaivan-holvissa|author=Harri Alanne|date=2012-03-19|accessdate=2020-02-02|work=yle.fi|language=fi|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150219001023/http://yle.fi/aihe/artikkeli/2012/03/19/prisma-studio-tuomiopaivan-holvissa|archive-date=2015-02-19|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="李珮雲"/>

由於[[斯瓦巴群島|斯瓦巴群島]]產[[煤礦|煤礦]]，為種子庫製冷機的動力提供原料來源，使其能進一步將種子冷卻至[[攝氏|攝氏]]−18℃的最佳溫度，
<ref name="regjeringen">{{cite web |url=http://www.regjeringen.no/en/dep/lmd/campain/svalbard-global-seed-vault/news/svalbard-global-seed-vault-from-safety-i.html |title=Svalbard Global Seed Vault: From safety in permafrost to optimal conditions |publisher=農業和食品部 |date=2008-05-20 |accessdate=2008-07-18 |language=en |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080802150534/http://www.regjeringen.no/en/dep/lmd/campain/svalbard-global-seed-vault/news/svalbard-global-seed-vault-from-safety-i.html?id=512006 |archivedate=2008-08-02 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Kinver"/>且即使製冷機發生故障，種子庫也需經過數周，溫度才可回升為當地氣溫攝氏-3℃，並估計需2世紀時間回升至0℃。<ref name="Woodward"/>根據種子庫建立前的可行性評估，種子庫可保存種子樣本數百年，其中一些重要作物則可維持數千年的生存能力。<ref name="Fowler2008">{{cite web|url=https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/57a08bc740f0b652dd000eac/Global_Crop_Diversity_Trust_Svalbard_Paper.pdf|title=The Svalbard Global Seed Vault: Securing the Future of Agriculture|publisher=Global Crop Diversity Trust|author=Cary Fowler|date=2008-02-26|accessdate=2020-02-03|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190725112438/https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/57a08bc740f0b652dd000eac/Global_Crop_Diversity_Trust_Svalbard_Paper.pdf|archive-date=2019-07-25|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[File:Svalbard_Global_Seed_Vault_(23273281972)_(cropped).jpg|thumb]]
種子庫入口處的上方是由挪威[[藝術家|藝術家]]{{link-no|戴維·桑恩|Dyveke Sanne}}設計的發光[[裝置藝術|裝置藝術]]《永恆的反射》（''Perpetual repercussion''）。<ref name="pubartnorway">{{cite web |url=http://publicartnorway.org/prosjekter/svalbard-global-seed-vault/ |title=Svalbard Global Seed Vault |publisher=KORO: Public Art Norway |accessdate=2016-04-14 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160428161038/http://publicartnorway.org/prosjekter/svalbard-global-seed-vault/ |archive-date=2016-04-28 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>挪威政府規定超過一定費用所興建的建築須包含藝術品，因此{{link-no|文化部 (挪威)|Kulturdepartementet (Norge)|挪威文化部}}邀請戴維·桑恩設計該作品，《永恆的反射》由數個高[[反射率|反射率]]的[[不銹鋼|不銹鋼]]、{{le|分色濾光鏡|Dichroic filter}}和不同尺寸的[[棱鏡|棱鏡]]所構成，夏季時會反射[[極光|極光]]，冬季則由200條[[光纖電纜|光纖電纜]]使該裝置發出柔和的[[綠松色|綠松色]]和白色。<ref name="croptrust-lighting">{{cite web |url=http://www.croptrust.org/main/arcticseedvault.php?itemid=852 |title=Svalbard Global Seed Vault: Lighting Installation |publisher=Crop Trust |accessdate=2011-07-03 |language=en |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723142330/http://www.croptrust.org/main/arcticseedvault.php?itemid=852 |archivedate=2011-07-23 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

種子庫4,500萬[[挪威克朗|挪威克朗]]的建設費用由挪威政府全額出資興建，於2006年6月19日舉行動土典禮，<ref name="regjeringen-faq"/><ref name="BBC 2006-06-19">{{Cite news|title=Work begins on Arctic seed vault|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/5094450.stm|work=BBC News|date=2006-06-19|accessdate=2020-01-03|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191221141300/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/5094450.stm|archive-date=2019-12-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>2008年2月26日正式完工啟用。<ref name="Mellgren"/><ref>{{Cite web|title=Ma nyílik a növények Noé bárkája|url=http://index.hu/tudomany/blog/2008/02/26/ma_nyilik_a_novenyek_noe_barkaja/|accessdate=2020-02-03|date=2008-02-26|last=Veronika|first=Munk|work=index.hu|language=hu|archive-date=2021-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210505221359/https://index.hu/tudomany/blog/2008/02/26/ma_nyilik_a_novenyek_noe_barkaja/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 管理 ==
[[File:Svalbard_seed_vault.jpg|thumb]]
种子库的常年运转费用大约为每年270萬[[挪威克朗|挪威克朗]]，<ref name="_Annual-ProgressReport2018">{{Cite web|title=Annual Progress Report 2018|url=https://www.nordgen.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/SeedVault_Annual-ProgressReport2018_Publ_June2019.pdf|accessdate=2020-02-02|author=|date=2019-06|format=PDF|publisher=NordGen|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190924083329/https://www.nordgen.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/SeedVault_Annual-ProgressReport2018_Publ_June2019.pdf|archive-date=2019-09-24|dead-url=yes}}</ref>主要由{{le|北歐遺傳資源中心|Nordic Genetic Resource Center}}負責管理，<ref>{{Cite web|title=Our Operations|url=https://www.seedvault.no/how-we-work/our-operations/|accessdate=2020-02-02|date=2017-07-12|work=Svalbard Global Seed Vault|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222151313/https://www.seedvault.no/how-we-work/our-operations/|archive-date=2019-12-22|dead-url=no}}</ref>包括庫內的營運、紀錄，以及與其他種子庫和基因庫長期保持聯繫，每年定期接收自世界各地捐贈和寄放的種子<ref name="Svalbard Global Seed Vault-Organisation"/><ref>{{Cite web|title=This Agronomist Is Safeguarding the World’s Seeds|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/bjy7z5/this-agronomist-is-safeguarding-the-worlds-seeds|accessdate=2020-02-02|date=2018-01-03|last=Flowers|first=Rebecca|work=Vice|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191221001355/https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/bjy7z5/this-agronomist-is-safeguarding-the-worlds-seeds|archive-date=2019-12-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[聯合國糧農組織|聯合國糧農組織]]與{{le|國際農業研究磋商組織|CGIAR}}合作成立的{{le|全球作物多樣性信託基金|Crop Trust}}與挪威政府提供營運資金並協助其管理，<ref name="Svalbard Global Seed Vault-Organisation"/>如透過各國的農業中心協助將種子包裝後運送至種子庫，<ref name="jia2014"/>該基金會的資金來自[[比爾及梅琳達·蓋茨基金會|比爾及梅琳達·蓋茨基金會]]、[[先正達|先正達基金會]]或[[美國政府|美國政府]]等組織及各國政府<ref name="donate"/>。

种子库可为世界各国的政府、組織或個人免費保存种子，委託方也需向種子庫簽署類似《{{le|糧食和農業作物遺傳資源國際公約|International Treaty on Plant Genetic Resources for Food and Agriculture}}》的存放協議，种子的所有权可以归委託方所有，其在任何时候都拥有取走种子的权利。<ref>{{Cite web|title=For depositors|url=https://www.seedvault.no/resources/depositors/|accessdate=2020-02-02|date=2017-07-12|work=Svalbard Global Seed Vault|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222151605/https://www.seedvault.no/resources/depositors/|archive-date=2019-12-22|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Global Citizens|url=https://www.seedvault.no/resources/global-citizens/|accessdate=2020-02-02|date=2017-07-12|work=Svalbard Global Seed Vault|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222151536/https://www.seedvault.no/resources/global-citizens/|archive-date=2019-12-22|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Retningslinjer for deponering av frø|url=https://www.nordgen.org/skand/global-seed-vault/guidelines-calender/|accessdate=2020-03-29|work=NordGen|language=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190716172349/https://www.nordgen.org/skand/global-seed-vault/guidelines-calender/|archive-date=2019-07-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>

種子庫於2019年的維護費用約為240萬挪威克朗。<ref name="annual2019"/>

== 历史 ==
自1984年開始，北歐基因銀行（Nordic Gene Bank）就透過[[冷凍|冷凍]]的方式將種子保存於斯瓦爾巴群島已廢棄的{{link-no|3號礦坑|Gruve 3}}內。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Svalbard globale frøhvelv: Det perfekte frølager|url=http://www.skogoglandskap.no/filearchive/svalbardfrolagereb.pdf|accessdate=2020-02-02|author=Even Bratberg|date=2007-12|format=PDF|publisher=Ås Nytt|language=no|dead-url=yes|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121205102400/http://www.skogoglandskap.no/filearchive/svalbardfrolagereb.pdf|archive-date=2012-12-05}}</ref>2008年1月，北歐基因銀行與另外兩個北歐基因保護組織合併成立{{le|北歐遺傳資源中心|Nordic Genetic Resource Center}}。<ref>{{Cite web|title=About us|url=https://www.nordgen.org/en/about-us/|accessdate=2020-01-05|work=NordGen|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190716141925/https://www.nordgen.org/en/about-us/|archive-date=2019-07-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>2001年，挪威政府完成《{{le|糧食和農業作物遺傳資源國際公約|International Treaty on Plant Genetic Resources for Food and Agriculture}}》並開放給各國政府締約，之後{{le|國際生物多樣性|Bioversity International}}組織與挪威政府接洽，提議在斯瓦爾巴群島建立一個全球性機構，挪威政府在受到[[聯合國糧食及農業組織|聯合國糧食及農業組織]]、{{le|國際農業研究磋商組織|CGIAR}}等組織支持後，<ref name="FAO"/>於2004年10月承諾出資興建斯瓦爾巴全球種子庫，並由{{le|全球作物多樣性信託基金|Crop Trust}}及北歐遺傳資源中心協助建造。<ref name="Svalbard Global Seed Vault">{{Cite web|title=History|url=https://www.seedvault.no/about/history/|accessdate=2020-01-05|date=2017-07-04|work=Svalbard Global Seed Vault|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222151520/https://www.seedvault.no/about/history/|archive-date=2019-12-22|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="Mellgren"/>

2006年6月19日，種子庫在時任[[挪威首相|挪威首相]]、[[瑞典首相|瑞典首相]]、[[芬蘭總理|芬蘭總理]]、[[丹麥首相|丹麥首相]]及[[冰岛总理列表|冰島總理]]等北歐五國領導人的參加下舉行動土典禮。<ref name="BBC 2006-06-19"/><ref>{{Cite web|title=Grundstein für globale Saatgut-Arche-Noah gelegt|url=https://www.heise.de/newsticker/meldung/Grundstein-fuer-globale-Saatgut-Arche-Noah-gelegt-133822.html|date=2006-06-19|accessdate=2020-02-02|last=Boeing|first=Niels|work=heise online|language=de|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181020135752/https://www.heise.de/newsticker/meldung/Grundstein-fuer-globale-Saatgut-Arche-Noah-gelegt-133822.html|archive-date=2018-10-20|dead-url=no}}</ref>
2007年，挪威政府、全球作物多樣性信託基金和北歐遺傳資源中心簽訂三方長期合作協議，<ref name="whatisnordgen"/><ref name="Svalbard Global Seed Vault"/>協議規定種子庫由{{le|農業和食品部 (挪威)|Ministry of Agriculture and Food (Norway)|挪威農業和食品部}}和{{le|公共建築和財產局 (挪威)|Norwegian Directorate of Public Construction and Property|挪威公共建築和財產局}}負責建造、維護，並且與全球作物多樣性信託基金共同負擔營運費用；北歐遺傳資源中心則負責管理、營運並記錄，長期與世界各國的基因庫保持聯絡，<ref name="Svalbard Global Seed Vault-Organisation">{{Cite web|title=The Organisation|url=https://www.seedvault.no/how-we-work/the-organisation/|accessdate=2020-01-05|date=2017-07-12|work=Svalbard Global Seed Vault|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222151602/https://www.seedvault.no/how-we-work/the-organisation/|archive-date=2019-12-22|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[聯合國農糧組織|聯合國農糧組織]]、{{le|國際農業研究磋商組織|CGIAR}}等組織組成國際諮詢小組（International Advisory Panel），負責監督、指導和對種子庫的管理提出建議。<ref name="jia2014">{{cite journal |url=https://jia.sipa.columbia.edu/files/2014/10/141-146_Fowler_Feature.pdf |title=A 'Doomsday' Seed Vault to Protect the World's Diversity — An interview with Cary Fowler |journal=Journal of International Affairs |first=Cary |last=Fowler |volume=67 |issue=2 |pages=141–146 |date=2014 |jstor=24461740 |language=en |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141209012746/https://jia.sipa.columbia.edu/files/2014/10/141-146_Fowler_Feature.pdf |archivedate=2014-12-09 |access-date=2020-01-05 |dead-url=no }}</ref>
种子库於2008年2月26日，種子庫正式竣工並舉行啟用典禮，時任[[歐洲聯盟|歐洲聯盟]][[歐盟執行委員會|執行委員會]]主席[[若泽·曼努埃尔·巴罗佐|若泽·曼努埃尔·巴罗佐]]、[[綠帶運動|綠帶運動]]發起人[[旺加里·马塔伊|旺加里·马塔伊]]、时任挪威首相[[延斯·斯托尔滕贝格|延斯·斯托尔滕贝格]]等近150人均出席參加。<ref name="Mellgren">{{Cite web|title=‘Doomsday’ seed vault opens in Arctic|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/23352014/ns/technology_and_science-science/t/doomsday-seed-vault-opens-arctic/|accessdate=2020-01-05|date=2008-02-27|last=Mellgren|first=Doug|work=msnbc.com|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171011142330/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/23352014/ns/technology_and_science-science/t/doomsday-seed-vault-opens-arctic/|archive-date=2017-10-11|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Tore Ulabrand Johansen">{{Cite web|title=En frossen edens hage|url=https://www.vg.no/i/ebnMg|author=Tore Ulabrand Johansen|date=2008-02-26|accessdate=2020-03-29|work=[[世界之路報|Verdens Gang]]|language=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080327025900/http://www.vg.no/nyheter/utenriks/klimatrusselen/artikkel.php?artid=518299|archive-date=2008-03-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>

{{抬升式引用|這是一個冰凍的[[伊甸園|伊甸園]]，一個無論世界上發生什麼事都可以永遠保留生命的地方。<br>''Dette blir en frossen edens hage. Et sted der livet kan bevares for all fremtid uansett hva som skjer rundt om i verden.''|[[歐盟執行委員會|歐盟執行委員會]]主席[[若澤·巴洛索|若澤·巴洛索]]<ref name="Tore Ulabrand Johansen"/>}}

首批種子於2008年1月抵達，種子樣本中約5％來自[[荷蘭|荷蘭]][[瓦赫寧恩大學|瓦赫寧恩大學]]下屬的荷蘭遺傳資源中心（CGN）。<ref name="Kinver">{{Cite news|title='Doomsday' seeds arrive in Norway|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7217821.stm|first=Kinver|last=Mark|date=2008-01-31|work=BBC News|accessdate=2020-01-19|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200111141753/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7217821.stm|archive-date=2020-01-11|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Opslag met miljarden zaden, voor tijden van oorlog|url=https://www.volkskrant.nl/gs-b7b0ccf6|accessdate=2020-01-19|date=2008-02-26|last=Aarden|first=Van onze verslaggeefster Marieke|work=de Volkskrant|language=nl}}</ref>
2009年，在種子庫啟用一周年之際，已儲存約90,000多種[[農作物|農作物]]種子的樣本，總種子數約達2000萬份、總重約4噸<ref name="time20090227">{{cite magazine |url=http://content.time.com/time/health/article/0,8599,1882288,00.html |title=The Planet's Ultimate Backup Plan: Svalbard |magazine=Time |first=Bryan |last=Walsh |date=2009-02-27 |accessdate=2009-03-01 |language=en-US |issn=0040-781X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929222328/http://content.time.com/time/health/article/0,8599,1882288,00.html |archive-date=2013-09-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>其中包括來自[[愛爾蘭|愛爾蘭]]國家基因庫（National gene banks）的32種[[馬鈴薯|馬鈴薯]]基因、2萬種來自[[美國|美國]]{{le|農業研究局|Agricultural Research Service}}的基因，其他則來自[[加拿大|加拿大]]、[[瑞士|瑞士]]、[[哥倫比亞|哥倫比亞]]、[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]及[[敘利亞|敘利亞]]等國的國際種子研究人員。<ref>{{Cite web|title=ARS ships more seeds to genebank facility in Norway|url=https://www.hpj.com/archives/ars-ships-more-seeds-to-genebank-facility-in-norway/article_167b5c52-102b-5c8a-bf32-157a17b08fdb.html|date=2009-03-02|accessdate=2020-01-19|work={{le|高原雜誌|High Plains Journal}}|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190716141923/https://www.hpj.com/archives/ars-ships-more-seeds-to-genebank-facility-in-norway/article_167b5c52-102b-5c8a-bf32-157a17b08fdb.html|archive-date=2019-07-16|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Young2009">{{cite news |url=http://www.allheadlinenews.com/articles/7014225215 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110525122251/http://www.allheadlinenews.com/articles/7014225215 |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2011-05-25 |title=Global Seed Vault Marks First Anniversary; 20 Million Seeds From One-Third Of Earth's Food Crops Now Stored In Case Of Disaster |work={{le|所有頭條新聞|All Headline News}} |first=Linda |last=Young |date=2009-02-26 |accessdate=2009-03-01 }}</ref><ref name="time20090227"/>截至該時，種子庫已儲存世界上主要農作物品種的3分之1，<ref name="Young2009"/>且為紀念種子庫啟用一周年，多名[[氣候變遷|氣候變遷]]及糧食生產專家於[[朗伊爾城|朗伊爾城]]召開為期3天的紀念會議，<ref>{{Cite news|title=More seeds for 'doomsday vault'|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7912543.stm|work=BBC News|date=2009-02-26|accessdate=2020-01-31|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190907055903/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/7912543.stm|archive-date=2019-09-07|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[日本|日本]][[雕刻家|雕刻家]]{{link-ja|田邊光彰|田辺光彰}}於會議上捐贈一個野生稻穗的雕塑品《THE SEED 2009 - MOMI IN SITU CONSERVATION》給種子庫，其在過去的20年中不斷提倡野生稻作的保護。<ref name="norwayjp2009">{{cite web |url=http://www.norway.or.jp/news_events/culture/visual_art/The_seed_2009 |script-title=ja:日本人彫刻家の作品が種子貯蔵庫へ |publisher=[[外交部_(挪威)|外交部]] |year=2009 |accessdate=2011-07-03 |language=ja |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120326134624/http://www.norway.or.jp/news_events/culture/visual_art/The_seed_2009/ |archivedate=2012-03-26 |dead-url=no }}</ref>2010年，由7名[[美國參議員|美國參議員]]所組成的代表團向種子庫捐贈一批北美的[[辣椒|辣椒]]種子。<ref>{{Cite news|title='Red hot' arrivals at seed vault|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/10603656|newspaper=BBC News|date=2010-07-13|accessdate=2020-02-01|language=en-GB|first=Mark|last=Kinver|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190716143423/https://www.bbc.com/news/10603656|archive-date=2019-07-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>截至2013年2月，種子庫儲存的种子样本数已達到774,601份。<ref name="Westengen2013">{{cite journal |title=Global Ex-Situ Crop Diversity Conservation and the Svalbard Global Seed Vault: Assessing the Current Status |journal=[[PLOS_ONE|PLOS ONE]] |first1=Ola T. |last1=Westengen |first2=Simon |last2=Jeppson |first3=Luigi |last3=Guarino |volume=8 |issue=5 |at=e64146 |date=May 2013 |doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0064146 |pmc=3650076 |pmid=23671707 |bibcode=2013PLoSO...864146W|language=en}}</ref>

2015年，位於敘利亞[[阿勒坡|阿勒坡]]的{{le|国际干旱地区农业研究中心|International Center for Agricultural Research in the Dry Areas}}為緩解[[中東地區|中東地區]]的生物多樣性因[[敘利亞內戰|敘利亞內戰]]而被嚴重破壞的問題，計畫於敘利亞與[[黎巴嫩|黎巴嫩]]接壤的[[貝卡谷地|貝卡谷地]]中建造另一座種子庫而向斯瓦爾巴全球種子庫提出申請，提取130箱糧食種子，<ref>{{Cite web|title=北極末日寶庫為人類留種|url=https://www.thestandnews.com/international/北極末日庫為人類留種/|accessdate=2020-02-02|date=2015-09-26|work=立場新聞 Stand News|language=zh-hk|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190818232110/https://thestandnews.com/international/%E5%8C%97%E6%A5%B5%E6%9C%AB%E6%97%A5%E5%BA%AB%E7%82%BA%E4%BA%BA%E9%A1%9E%E7%95%99%E7%A8%AE/|archive-date=2019-08-18|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Noelia Núñez">{{Cite web|title=La Bóveda del fin del mundo cumple 10 años|url=https://elfuturoesapasionante.elpais.com/la-boveda-del-fin-del-mundo-cumple-10-anos/|accessdate=2020-03-29|author=Noelia Núñez|date=2018-04-08|publisher=Vodafone España|work=El País Ediciones|language=es|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616053416/https://elfuturoesapasionante.elpais.com/la-boveda-del-fin-del-mundo-cumple-10-anos/|archive-date=2018-06-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>這是研究人員自種子庫啟用7年以來首次提取庫存中的種子。<ref>{{Cite news|title=Syrian war spurs first withdrawal from doomsday Arctic seed vault|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-seeds-idUKKCN0RL1KA20150921|author=Alister Doyle|newspaper=Reuters|date=2015-09-21|accessdate=2020-02-02|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724032736/https://uk.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-seeds-idUKKCN0RL1KA20150921|archive-date=2019-07-24|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=How a Seed Bank, Almost Lost in Syria’s War, Could Help Feed a Warming Planet|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/13/climate/syria-seed-bank.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2017-10-13|accessdate=2020-02-01|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Somini|last=Sengupta|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726120545/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/13/climate/syria-seed-bank.html|archive-date=2019-07-26|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ouzhou.oushinet.com/other/20150925/206337.html|title=叙利亚战火毁坏种子库 传说中的“诺亚方舟”要开仓放粮|accessdate=2015-12-25|author=|date=2015-09-25|work=|publisher=欧洲时报网|language=Zh-hans|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151225070447/http://ouzhou.oushinet.com/other/20150925/206337.html|archivedate=2015-12-25}}</ref>。該研究中心在成功復育數千種植物後，於2017年將種子返還給斯瓦爾巴全球種子庫。<ref name="George"/><ref>{{Cite web|title=Middle East Seeds Restored To World's 'Doomsday Vault', Two Years After Withdrawal Due To Syrian War|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dominicdudley/2017/02/22/middle-east-seeds-doomsday-vault/|date=2017-02-22|accessdate=2020-02-02|last=Dudley|first=Dominic|work=Forbes|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191023034118/https://www.forbes.com/sites/dominicdudley/2017/02/22/middle-east-seeds-doomsday-vault/|archive-date=2019-10-23|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Noelia Núñez"/>

2016年10月至2017年間，因[[氣候變遷|氣候變遷]]造成斯瓦巴群島當地溫度異常高於平均值，導致降雪量減少並持續降下[[暴雨|暴雨]]，<ref name="Mary Beth Griggs">{{Cite web|title=Turns out the Svalbard seed vault is probably fine|url=https://www.popsci.com/seed-vault-flooding/|author=Mary Beth Griggs|date=2017-05-22|accessdate=2020-02-01|work=Popular Science|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190915051657/https://www.popsci.com/seed-vault-flooding/|archive-date=2019-09-15|dead-url=no}}</ref>種子庫的入口因此遭到雨水和融化的永凍土入侵，水蔓延至隧道內約15公尺並結凍，並未進一步進入種子儲存庫而影響種子的保存。<ref name="Thuy">{{Cite web|title=Norway will spend $13 million to upgrade its doomsday seed vault|url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/2/26/17052690/doomsday-seed-vault-upgrade-13-million|accessdate=2020-02-01|date=2018-02-26|last=Ong|first=Thuy|work=The Verge|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201075826/https://www.theverge.com/2018/2/26/17052690/doomsday-seed-vault-upgrade-13-million|archive-date=2020-02-01|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Mary Beth Griggs"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wired.com/2017/05/arctic-doomsday-seed-vault-flooded-thanks-global-warming/|title=The Arctic Doomsday Seed Vault Flooded.|date=|accessdate=2020-02-03|author=|work=wired|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203102732/https://www.wired.com/2017/05/arctic-doomsday-seed-vault-flooded-thanks-global-warming/|archive-date=2019-12-03|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chinanews.com/gj/2017/05-21/8229789.shtml|title=全球暖化致北极地区融冰 “末日种子库”入口遭水淹|accessdate=2017-05-22|author=何路曼|date=2017-05-21|publisher=中新网|language=zh-cn|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170521075818/http://www.chinanews.com/gj/2017/05-21/8229789.shtml|archive-date=2017-05-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>{{link-no|氣候與環境部 (挪威)|Klima- og miljødepartementet|挪威氣候與環境部}}下轄的{{link-no|環境署 (挪威)|Miljødirektoratet|環境署}}於2018年發布一份報告，顯示斯瓦巴群島當地氣溫自1971至2017年已上升約3.5℃，<ref>{{Cite web|title=Climate in Svalbard 2100|url=https://www.miljodirektoratet.no/globalassets/publikasjoner/M1242/M1242.pdf|accessdate=2020-02-01|author=|date=2018|format=PDF|publisher={{link-no|環境署 (挪威)|Miljødirektoratet|環境署}}|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190905023401/https://www.miljodirektoratet.no/globalassets/publikasjoner/M1242/M1242.pdf|archive-date=2019-09-05|dead-url=no}}</ref>挪威氣象研究所也模擬2071至2100年的氣候變化情況，發現氣溫持續上升，暴雨、[[雪崩|雪崩]]等災害發生的機率將會提升，雪季亦會縮短，低海拔與沿海的永久凍土也將融化。<ref name="Alan Chiu"/>

2018年，挪威政府決定撥款1億挪威克朗改善種子庫設施，包括建造新的[[混泥土|混泥土]]通道、製冷設備和緊急[[電力系統|電力系統]]等裝置，<ref name="Thuy"/><ref name="Alister Doyle">{{Cite news|title=Norway to spend $13 million to upgrade 'doomsday' Arctic seed vault|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-norway-seeds-idUSKCN1G72EH|author=Alister Doyle|newspaper=[[路透社|Reuters]]|date=2018-02-23|accessdate=2020-03-29|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181128050753/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-norway-seeds-idUSKCN1G72EH|archive-date=2018-11-28|dead-url=no}}</ref>時任挪威農業和食品部長{{link-no|喬恩·喬治·戴爾|Jon Georg Dale}}在一份聲明中表示：<ref name="Woodward"/><ref name="regjeringen 2018-02-23">{{Cite web|title=The government proposes to allocate 100 million NOK to upgrade the Svalbard Global Seed Vault|url=https://www.regjeringen.no/en/aktuelt/the-government-proposes-to-allocate-100-million-nok-to-upgrade-the-svalbard-global-seed-vault/id2590668/|accessdate=2020-02-01|date=2018-02-23|last=|first=|work=農業和食品部|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191001191801/https://www.regjeringen.no/en/aktuelt/the-government-proposes-to-allocate-100-million-nok-to-upgrade-the-svalbard-global-seed-vault/id2590668/|archive-date=2019-10-01|dead-url=no}}</ref>
{{抬升式引用|保護對全球糧食安全至關重要的遺傳基因是一項重大且重要的任務。<br>''It is a great and important task to safeguard all the genetic material that is crucial to global food security.''}}
{{le|公共建築和財產局 (挪威)|Norwegian Directorate of Public Construction and Property|挪威公共建築和財產局}}也開始對隧道的防水工程進行改善，包括對隧道壁做防水處理、加蓋防水牆、移除隧道中的熱源及修建外部排水溝以防止融水在入口處匯聚，<ref>{{Cite web|title=Svalbard Global Seed Vault. Improvements|url=https://www.statsbygg.no/Nytt-fra-Statsbygg/Nyheter/2017/Svalbard-Global-Seed-Vault-Improvements/|date=2017-05-20|accessdate=2020-02-01|work={{le|公共建築和財產局 (挪威)|Norwegian Directorate of Public Construction and Property|公共建築和財產局}}|language=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222151323/https://www.statsbygg.no/Nytt-fra-Statsbygg/Nyheter/2017/Svalbard-Global-Seed-Vault-Improvements/|archive-date=2019-12-22|dead-url=no}}</ref>並將其排往深山。<ref name="Alister Doyle"/><ref>{{Cite web|title=千防萬防防不了暖化 挪威種子庫斥資百萬補強|url=https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/ch/news/3186736|date=2017-06-13|accessdate=2020-10-13|author=李昱德|work=[[台灣英文新聞|台灣英文新聞]]|language=zh-tw|archive-date=2019-08-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830160008/https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/ch/news/3186736|dead-url=no}}</ref>

